{
  "stem": "6130.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And there was-- the rabbi died some time ago, but it was like an assistant rabbi who was allowed to be there.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "But we pushed it, pushed it, pushed it, because we hoped that Imre would be back again.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "And my mother insisted that a son has to give the Kaddish at the funeral.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "And we waited, all of us, and I see he's running into the cemetery.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And he gave the Kaddish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And then we buried my father there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "And before he left, he came to me and to my niece.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "And he told us that he heard some horrible stories of Jewish women sent to the front and raped and killed.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "And whatever happens, we should avoid transportation wherever we will be, because that's what they do with young women.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "My niece was 19, and I was about 27.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And then-- and then he left, running and hiding and got back to camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "That's the last time, of course, I've seen him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "And when they talk about something hurts you, like a knife in your heart, that's true.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Because after I went back to Hungary in 1945, and I heard-- I knew what happened to my mother.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "I knew that in Auschwitz-- but then I heard about my brothers, and I was thinking about Imre, it was just like a knife in my heart.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "I had a sharp pain in my heart.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "I really did, for a long, long time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 75,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] After I got married, my husband-- of course, my second husband-- sent me to a psychiatrist, because I used to wake up in the night screaming for a long time.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
